Privacy Policy
Effective Date: January 1, 2023
Inspire Brands, Inc. (the “
Company
”) provides this Privacy Notice (“
Notice
”) to explain our practices regarding the collection and use of Personal Information about employees, contractors, and others who work for us (collectively, “
Team Members
”) and Job Applicants within the context of your employment or job application at Inspire Brands, Inc. and our following brands: Arby’s, Baskin-Robbins, Buffalo Wild Wings, Dunkin’, Jimmy Johns, and Sonic under their respective legal entities. This Notice explains what Personal Information we collect about Team Members and Job Applicants, why we collect it, how we use and share it, and the rights you have relating to your Personal Information under the California Consumer Privacy Act, as modified by the California Privacy Rights Act of 2020 (the “
CCPA
”) and any other applicable privacy regulation.
As used in this Notice, the term “
Personal Information
” means information that identifies, relates to, describes, is reasonably capable of being associated with, or could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, with you. Personal Information does not include information that is publicly available, de-identified, or aggregated.
To jump to our
Job Applicant Section
, please
click here
.
Cookie and Tracking Controls
To learn how to manage how we and our vendors use cookies and other tracking tools, and to read our Do Not Track Policy, click
here
.
